Class ConcurrentHashWeightedSet<T>

java.lang.Object
  com.davidsoergel.dsutils.collections.AbstractWeightedSet<T>
      com.davidsoergel.dsutils.collections.ConcurrentHashWeightedSet<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
MutableWeightedSet<T>, WeightedSet<T>, Serializable
public class ConcurrentHashWeightedSet<T>
extends AbstractWeightedSet<T>
implements MutableWeightedSet<T>

A WeightedSet backed by a HashMap. Note this is not thread-safe in any way (i.e., it does not use AtomicInteger and so forth the way the Google Multiset does).
